# Comparative Genome Analysis of Streptomyces silvae

## Dataset

The analysis includes two newly sequenced soil isolates and several publicly available genomes.

Newly sequenced strains:

- Streptomyces silvae TMS4I1
- Streptomyces silvae TMS12I2

Publicly available genomes downloaded from NCBI:

- Streptomyces silvae For3T
- Streptomyces sp. M3
- Streptomyces sp. gb1(2016)
- Streptomyces sp. ADI93-02
- Streptomyces sp. SID4921
- Streptomyces sp. LamerLS-316

## Read processing and genome assembly

Sequencing reads were processed using the Galaxy platform.

Quality control:
- FastQC

Read trimming:
- Trimmomatic

De novo assembly:
- Unicycler

Assembly polishing:
- Bowtie2
- Pilon

## Reference-guided scaffolding

Genome scaffolding was performed using RagTag.

Reference genome:
Streptomyces sp. M3

## Genome annotation

Genome annotation was performed using:

RASTtk (BV-BRC)

## Identification of related genomes

Related genomes were identified using the Similar Genome Finder tool from the BV-BRC database.

## Phylogenomic analysis

Phylogenomic classification and tree reconstruction were performed using the TYGS server (Type Strain Genome Server).

## Genome mining

Biosynthetic gene clusters (BGCs) were identified using antiSMASH.

Detected clusters included several conserved clusters such as:

- ectoine biosynthesis
- desferrioxamine siderophore clusters
- melanin biosynthesis
- alkylresorcinol clusters

In addition, several clusters showed low similarity to known reference clusters, suggesting the presence of potentially novel secondary metabolite pathways.

## Comparative genomics

Comparative genome analysis included:

- Average Nucleotide Identity (ANI)
- genome synteny analysis using Mauve
- comparison of biosynthetic gene cluster repertoires between strains

## Research focus

Comparative genomics and biosynthetic potential of Streptomyces silvae strains.
